    <section>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/69/Artificial_Intelligence_%26_AI_%26_Machine_Learning_-_30212411048.jpg" alt="AI Image">

        <p><strong>Artificial Intelligence (AI)</strong> is the simulation of human intelligence in machines that are programmed to think and learn like humans. These machines can perform tasks such as recognizing speech, solving problems, translating languages, and making decisions.</p>

        <h2>Types of AI</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Narrow AI:</strong> Designed to perform a specific task (like voice assistants or recommendation systems).</li>
            <li><strong>General AI:</strong> Has the ability to understand and learn any intellectual task a human can do.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Examples of AI</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Virtual assistants (e.g., Siri, Alexa)</li>
            <li>Self-driving cars</li>
            <li>Spam filters in email</li>
            <li>Facial recognition systems</li>
        </ul>

